<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Therefore" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Therefore,</orth> 1) for that: <cit><quote>t. my son i' the ooze is bedded,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 3, 100</bibl></cit> (in punishment for this). <cit><quote>what should I get t.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>t. we meet not now,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 1, 30</bibl></cit> (for this purpose). <cit><quote>lament t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 112</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we are t. provided,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 3</bibl></cit> (we are provided with what is necessary to perform this). <cit><quote>hath my sword t. broke through London gates, that you should leave me at the White Hart?</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.24" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 8, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou wilt revolt and fly to him, I fear. No, mighty liege; t. mistrust me not,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.479" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 479</bibl></cit> (as for this; concerning this). <cit><quote>often have you thanks t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.225" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 225</bibl>.<lb />2) on that account, accordingly, consequently: <bibl n="shak. ven 390" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 390</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 390" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 390</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 390" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 390</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 390" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 390</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 390" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 390</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.360" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 360</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.22.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.22.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.77.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 36</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 36</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.62" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 62</bibl>. 169 etc. etc.
